New Records: Quinton de Kock scored his third ODI hundred against Australia.
Key Match Events: Quinton de Kock scored 109 runs, leading South Africa to a total of 311 for 7.
Kagiso Rabada took 3 wickets for 33 runs.
Australia was bowled out for 177, resulting in a 134-run victory for South Africa.
Steven Smith was given out LBW after a DRS review overturned the on-field decision.
Marcus Stoinis was controversially given out caught down the leg side.
Australia missed seven chances in the field, contributing to their defeat.
Marnus Labuschagne and Mitchell Starc put together a defiant stand of 69 runs.
Pre-Game Insights: Australia made changes to their lineup, bringing in Josh Inglis and Marcus Stoinis for Alex Carey and Cameron Green.
Post-Match Reflections: Quinton de Kock's performance was a reminder of his status as a modern limited-overs great.
Australia needs to assess their own mistakes, including missed chances in the field.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was played in Lucknow on October 12, 2023.
Quinton de Kock announced that this tournament would be his last appearances in the ODI format.
